akas from release info: Game Shakers. Jak wydać grę? Poland

1.title: Babe Loves Danger
1.plot: Babe tries to plan the perfect date when she learns that Henry Hart is coming to New York to visit her.

2.title: Lumples
2.plot: A toy company hires the gang to make a game on a toy that they are not allowed to see.

3.title: Subway Girl
3.plot: When a video of Babe dancing to Dub's new music video goes viral, Dub challenges Babe to a dance battle to prove he is the better dancer.

4.title: Snackpot!
4.plot: Hudson and Trip open a vending machine that dispenses snacks at random on the subway; Dub quickly becomes obsessed with the device.

5.title: Babe & the Boys
5.plot: Babe and Kenzie's school project tops the gaming charts as an online sensation; rapper Double G finds out they used his song and comes to collect his share; despite their differences, the group teams up to create Game Shakers.

6.title: Escape from Utah!
6.plot: When Dub's brother shows up at Game Shakers and invites everyone except Dub to his wedding, the kids convince him to bring his brother into the fold, promising to make Dub behave himself at the event.

7.title: Super Ugly Head
7.plot: Kenzie is torn whether to tell on Dub after she sees him tear down his own statue.

8.title: Snoop Therapy
8.plot: The Game Shakers haven't been getting along;Dub recommends they see his therapist Snoop Dogg.

9.title: Flavor City
9.plot: The Game Shakers are given tickets to see Flavor City, but they feel sad when Dub can't come with them.

10.title: Hot Bananas
10.plot: Trip becomes depressed after losing a big video game battle to a 7-year-old.

11.title: Wet Willy's Wild Water Park
11.plot: The Game Shakers visit Wet Willy's Wild Water Park on its last day and try to break the all-time speed record for an extremely dangerous water slide, the Big Ripper.

12.title: Demolition Doll House
12.plot: Kenzie gets help from Babe to locate the boy who waved to her on the subway, while Trip and Hudson become obsessed with a model dollhouse.

13.title: Hungry Hungry Hypno
13.plot: Kenzie is hypnotized into being very hungry after the Game Shakers take her to a hypnotist for her birthday.

14.title: Breaking Bad News
14.plot: The Game Shakers accidentally break Dub's expensive new television and have to figure out how to break the news to him.

15.title: Bug Tussle
15.plot: Dub goes to Las Vegas and leaves Trip behind, so the Game Shakers take Trip to Dub's awesome apartment to show him a good time.

16.title: Boy Band Cat Nose
16.plot: Dub recommends Kenzie see an eccentric pet plastic surgeon to fix her cat's loud nose holes, while Trip tries to get Hudson into a boy band.

17.title: He's Back
17.plot: Babe is forced to choose between multiple boys from her past to go out with, while Trip and Hudson have to buy Dub a famous watch.

18.title: Why Tonya
18.plot: Trip tells the game shakers that he is in love with this girl tonya, so babe Kenzie and Hudson have to figure out a way to get him off of tonya's mind

1.title: Sky Whale
1.plot: Babe and Kenzie's school project becomes an online gaming sensation; rapper Double G finds out that Babe and Kenzie used his song in their game.

2.title: Lost Jacket, Falling Pigeons
2.plot: Babe buys herself a fancy new jacket after Dub gives the girls bonuses for Sky Whale's success; a flock of pigeons takes up residence in Game Shakers.

3.title: Dirty Blob
3.plot: After Trip accidentally destroys a copy of the Game Shakers' latest game, the gang must sneak into Dub's recording studio to retrieve the last remaining copy.

4.title: MeGo the Freakish Robot
4.plot: A company asks the Game Shakers to build a game based on a robot they created; the robot becomes depressed and malfunctions.

5.title: Tiny Pickles
5.plot: Babe and Kenzie's new game is ready, but Dub promises the world another game on a crazy dream he had.

6.title: Scared Tripless
6.plot: Double G asks Babe and Kenzie to help him scare Triple G on Halloween, but the girls decide to reveal his plan to Triple G.

7.title: Trip Steals the Jet
7.plot: Feeling pressure to fit in with Trip's rich friends, Babe convinces Trip to borrow Dub's jet for the night.

8.title: Lost on the Subway
8.plot: The Game Shakers take the subway to a boxing game pitch, but forget the gloves and send Trip and Hudson back for them.

9.title: You Bet Your Bunny
9.plot: The Game Shakers host a tournament to promote a new Sky Whale update; Double G bets Bunny, thinking Babe will beat one of her classmates.

10.title: A Reggae Potato Christmas
10.plot: When the Game Shakers visit Double G on the set of his Christmas special, an accident during the opening number forces them to finish the show without him.

11.title: Poison Pie
11.plot: After getting noise complaints from their neighbor, Babe and Kenzie decide to bake him a pie to make amends.

12.title: Party Crashers
12.plot: Babe and Kenzie's plans to hang with Mason are ruined when Bunny and Ruthless crash a birthday party; Dub uses Hudson to make Trip jealous when Trip chooses work over hanging out with him.

13.title: The Girl Power Awards
13.plot: When Babe and Kenzie are nominated for a Girl Power Award, Kenzie quickly realizes that the award show is a scam.

14.title: A Job for Jimbo
14.plot: The Game Shakers work to finish creating a new ocean pollution game; Dub hopes to score a duet with a famous singer, so he makes the company hire her step-grandson.

15.title: Shark Explosion
15.plot: Triple G's mom Jackie invites the Game Shakers on her yacht to see fireworks. But she and Double G have doubled booked the yacht, causing Dub to compete with her for the kids' affection.

16.title: Nasty Goats
16.plot: When the gang discovers that a hacker has put their new game on an illegal Web site, they track him down in Alaska.

17.title: Babe's Fake Disease
17.plot: Kenzie invites an uninterested Babe to her coding club; Babe swoons when she meets a member of Kenzie's coding club; an aging app predicts that Trip will go bald.

18.title: The Diss Track
18.plot: When a rival rapper releases a track about Double G, the Game Shakers convince him to release a response track.

20.title: Revenge at Tech Fest
20.plot: The Game Shakers have the Girls Who Code help them when an old rival of Double G's returns for revenge.

1.title: Armed & Coded
1.plot: Babe convinces Kenzie to teach Mason Kendal coding, but then gets jealous when Kenzie starts spending more and more time with him.

2.title: The Secret Level
2.plot: Hudson releases false information about a secret level in a Game Shakers' game; Babe goes on a date with Mason Kendal.

3.title: The Very Old Finger
3.plot: While visiting a mummy exhibit, Hudson accidentally snaps off a mummy's finger and Babe leads a quest to glue it back on without getting caught.

4.title: Buck the Magic Rat
4.plot: When Kenzie saves a rat in the subway, the gang starts to believe that the rat is bringing them good luck.

5.title: Baby Hater
5.plot: The Game Shakers step up to help Dub get over his fear of babies when it threatens his recently announced bid for mayor.

6.title: Byte Club
6.plot: Trip beats a gaming legend, landing him a sponsorship deal with a big company. When the deal turns out to be a nightmare, Dub and the kids must help Trip tarnish his reputation and lose his contract.

7.title: Babe's Bench
7.plot: Babe blows the entire Game Shakers ad budget on a high-tech bus bench, only to find out the bench is a magnet for low-life's and weirdos.

8.title: The Mason Experience
8.plot: Babe is upset to learn that Mason Kendal is moving, so Kenzie designs her a virtual reality version of Mason.

9.title: Bunger Games
9.plot: When pop star Kayla Batch hires The Game Shakers to make a lifestyle game, she invites Babe to join her elite squad while Kenzie is left on the outs.

10.title: Wedding Shower of Doom
10.plot: When Dub's brother shows up at Game Shakers and invites everyone except Dub to his wedding, the children convince him to bring his brother into the fold, promising to make Dub behave himself at the event.

11.title: Bear Butt Laser Runner
11.plot: After learning that the exact same game idea they are about to pitch to a client was already released by another company, the Game Shakers have 20 minutes to think up a new game.

12.title: Air TnP
12.plot: After the Game Shakers sign up for a restroom-sharing app, one of their customers sabotages their new game with a virus, and the Game Shakers have to figure out a way to undo the damage.

13.title: Llama Llama Spit Spit
13.plot: The Game Shakers are kicked out of Fooders for a guest who has his photo on the wall. Babe is aiming to get her own photo on the wall, which is necessary to get in.

14.title: Clam Shakers: Part 1
14.plot: When Game Shakers tries to collaborate with The Clam Jumper, they face new problems.

15.title: Clam Shakers: Part 2
15.plot: A failed hacking attempt and blackmail put the Game Shakers' big deal with Clam Jumper in jeopardy.

16.title: Wing Suits & Rocket Boots
16.plot: The Game Shakers set Hudson up with a let's play account to help promote their games, but things quickly get out of hand when Hudson puts on Dub's rocket boots for fun.

17.title: Game Shippers
17.plot: The Game Shakers are tracking down Nathan Kress to find out which ICarly girl he liked more - Carly or Sam.

18.title: The One with the Coffee Shop
18.plot: After an online story about Game Shakers snubs Kenzie, she and Babe get in a fight. Upset, Kenzie takes a job as a waitress at a coffee shop and Babe has to try and get her back to Game Shakers.

19.title: The Trip Trap
19.plot: Babe and Kenzie are suspicious of Trip's new fame-hungry girlfriend and are determined to find out if she's using him to get closer to Double G.

20.title: The Switch
20.plot: When Dub and the Game Shakers swap Bunny for Hudson, the Game Shakers quickly regret it and have to figure out how to get Hudson back.

21.title: Dancing Kids, Flying Pig
21.plot: In order to finish their new dance game on time, The Game Shakers have to wear a motion capture suit and dance their way through the next 48 hours.

22.title: War and Peach
22.plot: In an attempt to get to know each other better and increase productivity, Kenzie organizes a team building retreat.

23.title: Spy Games
23.plot: After Kenzie installs security cameras, Babe and Trip try to teach her a lesson about spying on people.

24.title: Babe Gets Crushed
24.plot: After Trip fervently asks Babe for some Romantic advise for his friend 'Chuck', she comes to the suspicion that Trip is having a crush on her and tries everything to avoid an embarrassing situation at work.

imdb.plot outline: A live-action sitcom about two 12-year-old girls who start a multi-million-dollar gaming company and take on rap superstar Double G as a business partner. As part of a multi-platform experience, the games seen in the episodes will be released through apps and online from Nickelodeon.
